    "By (3.2), we see that the left hand side of (3.3) is well defined and, by the definition of ∼, it equals the right hand side if and only ifj i T (f i,j, π i,j) = j ⟨ω j, T ⟩ for every T ∈ P d.However, this equality follows immediately from the definition of the pairing, (3.1) and (3.2).Here we connect potential forms and the canonical embedding to Lipschitz regularity.Theorem 3.10.",
